# Rust build artifacts
/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Test artifacts
/tmp-test-*/

# Claude Code (commands and settings are local; CLAUDE.md is untracked too — ADR-118
# delta 7: a public, mergeable CLAUDE.md is an instruction-injection surface for AI-assisted
# sessions. It becomes a symlink into the Huldr vault like the docs below.)
.claude/
CLAUDE.md

# Project-management documentation (kept locally, not published)
# Everything in the 9*-* range is internal: ideas, plans, journals, reports,
# project supervisor (status/roadmap/registry), and the archive.
# Topic-oriented docs (00-foundation, 10-operations, 20-reference) stay tracked
# — they're the public engineering record. The internal documentation guide
# itself (contributing-internal.md) stays local; CONTRIBUTING.md is its public
# counterpart.
#
# No trailing slash on these six: they become symlinks into the Huldr vault
# (~/Huldr/projects/urd/), and trailing-slash gitignore patterns match real
# directories only, not symlinks — a trailing slash here would silently
# un-ignore the symlink itself.
docs/90-archive
docs/95-ideas
docs/96-project-supervisor
docs/97-plans
docs/98-journals
docs/99-reports
docs/contributing-internal.md
# Local scripts and prompts stay private; tracked dev tooling is whitelisted below.
scripts/*
!scripts/install-hooks.sh
!scripts/pre-commit.sh
!scripts/pre-commit-pii.sh
!scripts/check-vault-boundary.sh
!scripts/check-docs.sh
!scripts/check-registry.sh
!scripts/check-present-not-journey.sh
!scripts/staging-reset.sh
!scripts/check.sh
!scripts/release-preflight.sh
!scripts/release-bump.sh
!scripts/collect-diagnostics.sh
